
Install Go
Install Git
Install any IDE (Visual Studio Code)
Create GOPATH env variable
    Note: no need to set this env variable if the default location is used to setup workspace (which is ~/go/).
Create GOROOT env variable if not already created by the install go step. 
    Note: no need to set this env variable if the default location is used to install go (which is ??????? on mac, and C:\go on windows).
Create src folder in GOPATH
(in src folder) Create one new folder for each project
